name: tower silo production, plastic | tower silo, plastic | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/3786/documentation

This dataset represents an example of a typical tower silo. The module includes a foundation made of concrete and a tower silo made of glass fibre reinforced polyester. Size: 105 m3. Lifetime of the building is 25 years. The Functional Unit is one m3 of tower silo storage during entire service life.;This dataset represents an example of a typical tower silo. The module includes a foundation made of concrete and a tower silo made of glass fibre reinforced polyester. Size: 105 m3. Lifetime of the building is 25 years. The Functional Unit is one m3 of tower silo storage during entire service life..;Obs: The following limitation on the use of individual modules should be noted: to obtain realistic values when applying the modules, building sizes should not differ too widely from the sizes on which the module calculations were based. An acceptable approximation can be achieved for building sizes within a range of about half to twice the value of the calculated size of the modules. A wider difference would not be reasonable, since the type of construction would be too different from the calculated module.

From unoccupied land foreseen for a tower silo installation.

This acitivity ends with the final treatment and disposal of the building. The dataset includes the use of construction materials and building machines (hydraulic diggers, skid-steer loaders) for construction and also materials for repair and replacement. Waste disposal is inlcuded for repair, replacement and dismantling materials from the building infrastructure.  The dataset doesn't include direct emissions from construction, waste disposal of production and the resources used during utilization phase of the building. Disposal of construction waste such as packing materials and remnants of construction materials were not considered because it represents only a small proportion of the overall disposal quantity.
category: F:Construction/41:Construction of buildings/410:Construction of buildings/4100:Construction of buildings

processDocumentation.geographyDescription: The inventory applies for Swiss agricultural buildings only, because of the solid method of construction.
processDocumentation.technologyDescription: Based on selected examples of this type of housing and buildings commonly found in Switzerland in the year 2000;  but not conform to an “average Swiss building style”.
processDocumentation.samplingDescription: The inventory is calculated based on a solid database of agricultural buildings.
